      <textAnnotation id="sid-5142449E-CE8F-4199-A6C9-1C1383926255" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Process Tower: Procure To Pay
Process Group: Logistics Management Inbound
Process: LI-200-100 Issue Waiver Request
</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-8CB5F26A-9F6E-470F-9138-AD95EEB9AAB8" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>L3 Description:
Confirm that failed material cannot be reworked and determine if a waiver is required. Generate a request for waiver on failed material and circulate to appropriate approval parties (i.e. production operations, customers, etc.). A request for waiver is a request to use material that has failed an inspection or quality requirement.
</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-B779EE22-EDBF-4EE4-B00C-A859CCE96E19" signavio:alignment="left">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioDictionaryLink propertyId="name">
               <signavio:dictionaryLink>/glossary/87e190e5800648088193185674a9aceb</signavio:dictionaryLink>
            </signavio:signavioDictionaryLink>
            <signavio:signavioType dataObjectType="IT-System"/>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bgcolor" metaValue="#e1e1e1"/>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>SAP S/4HANA</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-4C3B796E-AF78-4623-9150-D169FF636FB2" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>This would be performed manually outside SAP system
</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-C254039D-9E16-4D24-BE34-EC61D9F295D4" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Valuate if the failed material can be reworked or repaired?
</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-A4C12907-0B3F-4DCB-9D0D-0581068E1508" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Waiver Process Steps –
Document the details of the failed material, including inspection results, and quality requirements not met.
Assess if a waiver is required to use the failed material
Create a formal request for waiver document and get the approvals from the appropriate parties.
Based on the approval outcome, proceed with the next steps.
If approved, use the material
If not approved, determine alternative actions (e.g., scrap, return to supplier)
</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-782BF136-243A-4985-9F38-184AB988D865" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Return of discrepant materials to supplier is applicable where it is allowed by law.</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-04A4BD40-D22B-4F61-95F6-6F617BE4858D" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="#ff0000" fontFamily="" fontSize="" italic="" ref="text-left"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="#ff0000" fontFamily="" fontSize="" italic="" ref="text-right"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Flow has been migrated to BIC. Please inform the process steward Dhanwantry, Kalyan R &lt;kalyan.r.dhanwantry@intel.com&gt; and BPM Champions D'Elia, Traci &lt;traci.delia@intel.com&gt;,Newman, Jennifer &lt;jennifer.newman@intel.com&gt;of any design changes that occur within the flow moving forward. This will enable us to reflect those changes in the BIC and WIKI business process documentation.</text>
      </textAnnotation>
   </process>
